59. ervom B. ervum BbFZ. servom Ba. servum CD. daturin’, so Pylad. The MSS. have daturi. Bubus B. Bobus the rest.

60. Date aes si non estis, so Vulg. The MSS. are all corrupt here. Data es inonestis B, and so Bb with an h above the o. Datae si non estis Bc. Date es inhoneste C. Dataesinhonestis D. Dato aes inhonestis F Z. R has remodelled the line—

Date, si non estis: [ceterum] agite pergite— where he considers estis as equivalent to editis. W has Date aes, si ne estis. We have retained the Vulgate, but the text must be regarded as

quite uncertain. W. places a comma after agite, the Vulg. after porro.

61. Quoniam B. qffo a contraction for quoniam in CD. Quomodo F. Vulg. Quo ZW. occepisti CD. bibite Bc. bibi BaCD.

62. ffrcite, so Camer. The MSS. are very corrupt. ec ferite B. ecfer-ute CDa. cff’rite Db. ac serite FZ. R writes ecfercite. caedite B. cedite the rest of the MSS. The reading is not satisfactory.
